
Symptoms:
- VM sluggish or unresponsive
- Services slow to respond
- System becomes unstable
- “Out of memory” errors in logs

Diagnosis:
free -h
htop
docker stats
ps aux –sort=-%mem | head -10
ps aux –sort=-%cpu | head -10

Common Causes:
- Service memory leak
- Too many services for available RAM
- Log ingestion issues (Loki processing too much)
- Runaway container
- Misconfigured service (infinite loop)

Solutions:

For runaway container:
docker stats –no-stream
# Identify problem container
docker compose restart [service]

For Loki/Promtail issues:
# Check Promtail config limits log sources
cat /etc/promtail/promtail-config.yml
# Should only scrape auth.log and syslog, not all logs

For general high usage:
# Restart problem service
docker compose restart [service]

# Or reboot VM if unstable
ssh jireland@[host]
sudo reboot

For permanent fix:
# Increase VM RAM in Proxmox (if available)
# Or reduce number of running services
# Or optimize service configs (reduce retention, cache size, etc.)

Prevention:
- Monitor resource usage regularly via Grafana
- Set up alerts for high memory/CPU
- Limit log retention periods
- Configure Promtail to exclude self-referential logs
